---
import Feature from '../../layouts/Feature.astro';
---

<Feature
  title="DAEMON MODE"
  subtitle="Persistent sessions, crash recovery, reconnect anytime."
>
  <h2>Sessions Persist</h2>
  <p>ori-term separates your shell sessions from the window. A background process keeps your shells running even when you close the window. Reopen ori-term and pick up exactly where you left off -- scrollback, working directories, and all.</p>
  <p>A single-process mode is available as a fallback for sandboxed environments.</p>

  <h2>Auto-Save</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Layout saved automatically</strong> -- Window positions, tabs, pane layout, and working directories are saved every 30 seconds</li>
    <li><strong>Crash recovery</strong> -- If anything goes wrong, ori-term detects it on next launch and offers to restore your session</li>
    <li><strong>Safe writes</strong> -- Session files are written safely to prevent corruption from unexpected shutdowns</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Smart Output Handling</h2>
  <p>ori-term prioritizes responsiveness where it matters:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>The pane you are working in updates instantly</li>
    <li>Visible but unfocused panes update at display refresh rate</li>
    <li>Background panes update less frequently to save resources</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Remote Shells</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>SSH</strong> -- Open remote shells via SSH with agent forwarding and keepalive</li>
    <li><strong>WSL</strong> -- Windows Subsystem for Linux integration with auto-detection</li>
    <li>Run local and remote shells side by side in the same window</li>
  </ul>
</Feature>
